<subsection xml:id="C7.S13.SS2">
<title>Zeros of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.m1">\operatorname{erfc}z</Math></title>                  
<para xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="25" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.s1">
In the sector <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.m1">\tfrac{1}{2}\pi&lt;\operatorname{ph}z&lt;\tfrac{3}{4}\pi</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.m2">\operatorname{erfc}z</Math> has an infinite set of zeros <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.m3">z_{n}=x_{n}+iy_{n}</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.m4">n=1,2,3,\dots</Math> , arranged in order of increasing absolute value.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="26" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.s2">
The other zeros of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.m5">\operatorname{erfc}z</Math> are <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.m6">\overline{z}_{n}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="27" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.s3">
The zeros of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.m7">w\left(z\right)</Math> are <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.m8">iz_{n}</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS2.p1.m9">i\overline{z}_{n}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
