<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="75" xml:id="C7.S13.SS3.p3.s1">
As <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS3.p3.m1">n\to\infty</Math> the <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS3.p3.m2">x_{n}</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS3.p3.m3">y_{n}</Math> corresponding to the zeros of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S13.SS3.p3.m4">C\left(z\right)</Math> satisfy <Math equation-number="7.13.5" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S13.E5">x_{n}\sim\lambda+\frac{\alpha(\alpha\pi-4)}{8\pi\lambda^{3}}+\cdots,y_{n}\sim\frac{\alpha}{2\lambda}+\cdots, ,</Math> with <Math equation-number="7.13.6" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S13.E6">\lambda=\sqrt{4n-1},\alpha=(2/\pi)\ln\left(\pi\lambda\right)</Math>.
